<subSubSection pageId="101" pageNumber="102" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="101.[123,652,1220,1741]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
COMMENTS: In the original description, the type was said to be an adult male in the Rothschild Collection from Temangoh collected by Boden Kloss on 
<date box="[456,621,1484,1507]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" value="1911-07-24">24 July 1911</date>
, a misprint that was corrected without comment by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hartert, E." box="[161,396,1542,1565]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="425 - 505" refId="ref96767" refString="Hartert, E. 1920. Types of birds in the Tring Museum. B. Types in the general collection (contd.). Novitates Zoologicae 27: 425 - 505." type="journal article" year="1920">Hartert (1920: 478)</bibRefCitation>
. The above specimen is the only one collected at Temangoh that came to AMNH with the Rothschild Collection, and it bears the Rothschild type label. 
<typeStatus box="[123,236,1660,1683]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Paratypes</typeStatus>
are AMNH 591577â€“591578 and 591580â€“591586.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="101.[123,652,1220,1741]" lastBlockId="101.[699,1228,193,392]" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">
In their recent molecular studies of babÂ­ blers in the genera 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1836" box="[925,1007,193,216]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Yuhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[925,1007,193,216]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Yuhina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority=", Cibois et al. (2002: 385 - 386)" authorityName="Cibois" authorityPageNumber="385 - 386" authorityYear="2002" class="Aves" family="Timaliidae" genus="Stachyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1067,1175,193,216]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Stachyris</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cibois, A. &amp; M. V. Kalyakin &amp; H. Lian-Xian &amp; E. Pasquet" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" pagination="380 - 390" refId="ref91762" refString="Cibois, A., M. V. Kalyakin, H. Lian-Xian, and E. Pasquet. 2002. Molecular phylogenetics of babblers (Timaliidae): revaluation of the genera Yuhina and Stachyris. Journal of Avian Biology 33: 380 - 390." type="journal article" year="2002">Cibois et al. (2002: 385â€“386)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
found that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blyth" baseAuthorityYear="1844" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Yuhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zantholeuca">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Yuhina zantholeuca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not closely related to typical members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1836" box="[970,1052,281,304]" class="Aves" family="Zosteropidae" genus="Yuhina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[970,1052,281,304]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Yuhina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and suggested resurrection of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hodgson, 1844" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1844" class="Aves" family="Vireonidae" genus="Erpornis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="101" pageNumber="102" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1002,1105,311,334]" italics="true" pageId="101" pageNumber="102">Erpornis</emphasis>
Hodgson, 1844
</taxonomicName>
, for this species, pending further studies on its exact relationships.
</paragraph>
